-- Egypt Earmarks Additional $150 Million for Fuel Purchases
-- B y   A b d e l   L a t i f   W a h b a
-- 2012-06-07T13:19:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-07/egypt-earmarks-additional-150-million-for-fuel-purchases.html
Egypt ’s  Finance Ministry  said it
allocated an additional $150 million for fuel purchases to
ensure adequate supplies in the market and took “urgent
measures” to ensure that other commodities are available.  The additional funds raised to $4.5 billion dollars the
amount given to the Egyptian General Petroleum Corp., Finance
Minister Momtaz el-Saieed said in a statement today. He didn’t
say over what period the funding had been provided.  While the government had budgeted 40 billion pounds ($6.6
billion) for fuel subsidies from December through May, the
actual outlay amounted to 59 billion Egyptian pounds, Prime
Minister Kamal el-Ganzouri told journalists yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
